cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with using deep neural networks for solving inverse problems in computational imaging, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of information theory and machine learning techniques, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves simulations and experiments, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories.
